			 individual to the extent practicable;

paragraph.text:
The term registered apprenticeship program means a program registered under the Act of August 16, 1937 (commonly known as the 
            National Apprenticeship Act
          ; 50 Stat. 664, chapter 663; 
            29 U.S.C. 50 et seq.
          ).

